19
00:00:18,731 --> 00:00:22,777
<i>As the Clone War scorches
its destructive path across the galaxy,</i>

20
00:00:22,818 --> 00:00:26,239
<i>it is the Jedi who bring order to the chaos.</i>

21
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:29,951
<i>Though as the war progresses,
the number of Jedi have declined,</i>

22
00:00:30,076 --> 00:00:32,662
<i>and new younglings are harder to find.</i>

23
00:00:32,787 --> 00:00:36,165
<i>When a youngling is located,
they are brought to the Jedi Temple</i>

24
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:40,294
<i>and learn quickly
that their true family is now the Jedi Order.</i>

25
00:00:40,795 --> 00:00:43,756
<i>The trials are hard, tests must be passed,</i>

26
00:00:43,798 --> 00:00:46,801
<i>but none is as important as The Gathering.</i>

27
00:00:47,134 --> 00:00:51,305
<i>It is then that a Jedi's path will truly begin.</i>

28
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:56,310
Hurry, younglings.

29
00:00:58,813 --> 00:01:01,440
You have proved to be
the top of your class,

30
00:01:01,482 --> 00:01:04,610
and so now is the time of The Gathering.

31
00:01:04,652 --> 00:01:08,197
For a Jedi,
there is no greater challenge or honor.

32
00:01:11,492 --> 00:01:14,328
What is The Gathering, Padawan Tano?

33
00:01:15,496 --> 00:01:16,789
Petro,

34
00:01:17,331 --> 00:01:18,541
Ganodi,

35
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:19,834
Byph,

36
00:01:19,875 --> 00:01:21,210
Katooni,

37
00:01:21,794 --> 00:01:22,962
Zatt,

38
00:01:23,004 --> 00:01:24,505
and Gungi,

39
00:01:24,964 --> 00:01:28,509
the time has come
for you to build your own lightsabers.

40
00:01:28,634 --> 00:01:30,219
-I knew it!
-That's so wizard!

41
00:01:30,344 --> 00:01:32,179
-Whoa!
-I knew it!

42
00:01:32,221 --> 00:01:37,310
Be warned, this is no simple task,
and many perils lie ahead of you.

43
00:01:37,518 --> 00:01:42,356
Where we are going,
there is no place more sacred to the Jedi.

44
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:19,560
Not the most hospitable place.

45
00:02:19,602 --> 00:02:21,729
I think that's the point.

46
00:02:40,581 --> 00:02:42,458
It's a dead end.

47
00:02:44,919 --> 00:02:49,715
Younglings, outstretch your hands
and focus the Force.

48
00:02:49,757 --> 00:02:53,386
Together, and only together, can we enter.

49
00:03:30,506 --> 00:03:34,176
Now hurry. The sun has already risen,
and we must begin.

50
00:03:49,525 --> 00:03:51,152
Master Yoda.

51
00:03:53,112 --> 00:03:56,741
The Force made physical, a Jedi is.

52
00:03:56,866 --> 00:03:59,952
Comes great responsibility with that. Yes?

53
00:04:02,163 --> 00:04:04,832
Protect others, how does a Jedi? Hmm?

54
00:04:07,293 --> 00:04:09,545
Build your own lightsaber, you shall.

55
00:04:09,628 --> 00:04:13,382
But first, harvest your crystal,
each one of you must.

56
00:04:13,466 --> 00:04:14,508
-See, I told you !
-No, I told you.

57
00:04:14,592 --> 00:04:15,718
Yoda! Wow.

58
00:04:15,801 --> 00:04:16,886
No, I told you.

59
00:04:17,887 --> 00:04:21,348
The heart of the lightsaber, the crystal is.

60
00:04:21,432 --> 00:04:24,310
Focuses the Force from the Jedi, it does.

61
00:04:55,841 --> 00:05:01,347
If Jedi you are to become,
enter the Crystal Cave, you must.

62
00:05:02,097 --> 00:05:03,974
Trust yourself,

63
00:05:04,058 --> 00:05:05,518
trust each other,

64
00:05:05,601 --> 00:05:08,312
and succeed, you will.

65
00:05:09,563 --> 00:05:13,818
Once you have found your crystal,
do not remain inside.

66
00:05:13,901 --> 00:05:19,031
As daylight ends, the door will freeze
over again, and you will be trapped.

67
00:05:20,074 --> 00:05:21,534
For how long?

68
00:05:21,617 --> 00:05:26,288
For one rotation. There will be nothing
anyone can do for you.

69
00:05:26,372 --> 00:05:28,707
How will we know which crystal to pick?

70
00:05:29,542 --> 00:05:32,795
Only you can know which one is yours.
Now hurry.

71
00:05:48,602 --> 00:05:53,983
How do they expect us to find our crystals
when the whole place is made up of ice?

72
00:05:54,066 --> 00:05:58,612
I don't see the big deal though.
I could easily last a night in here.

73
00:05:58,696 --> 00:06:00,531
From my calculations,

74
00:06:00,614 --> 00:06:04,201
taking into account
the planetary movements in this system,

75
00:06:04,285 --> 00:06:08,664
um, the sun only rises
on Ilum every 19 days.

76
00:06:08,747 --> 00:06:11,292
That's a very long night.

77
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:14,461
Well, I don't know about you lot,
but enough with the chatter.

78
00:06:14,545 --> 00:06:17,339
I'm going to be the first
to get my crystal and get out of here.

79
00:06:17,423 --> 00:06:21,302
Petro, wait.
Maybe we should stay together.

80
00:06:21,385 --> 00:06:24,013
No, thank you. You're on your own.

81
00:06:25,389 --> 00:06:27,725
Come on, we need to keep moving.

82
00:06:31,395 --> 00:06:34,565
You're right. He is selfish.

83
00:06:47,202 --> 00:06:49,872
Uh, which way now?

84
00:06:49,955 --> 00:06:51,248
We don't have much time,

85
00:06:51,332 --> 00:06:53,626
and we have no idea
where the crystals are.

86
00:06:53,709 --> 00:06:55,544
We need to break into groups.

87
00:06:55,628 --> 00:06:57,129
What? No!

88
00:06:58,714 --> 00:07:00,799
Are we Jedi or cowards?

89
00:07:00,883 --> 00:07:03,636
On the count of three,
close your eyes and point to a door,

90
00:07:03,719 --> 00:07:06,680
and that's the direction each of us will go.

91
00:07:07,222 --> 00:07:10,684
One, two, three.

92
00:07:18,025 --> 00:07:21,153
Uh, sorry, Byph.
Looks like you're on your own.

93
00:07:23,739 --> 00:07:26,951
Byph, your instincts
told you to go that way.

94
00:07:27,034 --> 00:07:29,662
You have to follow your instincts.

95
00:07:32,456 --> 00:07:36,627
You shouldn't be afraid of monsters, Byph !
You're a Jedi.

96
00:08:02,403 --> 00:08:04,279
That must be a crystal.

97
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,805
I don't think this is the right way.

98
00:08:30,055 --> 00:08:32,349
We better go back.

99
00:08:33,809 --> 00:08:35,894
Wait. Up there, look!

100
00:08:36,979 --> 00:08:38,856
Something's flashing.

101
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:44,111
-I can't see anything.
-Why can't you see it?

102
00:08:44,194 --> 00:08:46,530
Maybe because it's your crystal.

103
00:08:46,613 --> 00:08:49,366
They said only we would know.

104
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:50,951
You'll have to climb.

105
00:08:51,035 --> 00:08:52,119
But up there?

106
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:55,330
It's just so high.

107
00:08:55,873 --> 00:08:57,791
I can't do that.

108
00:08:57,875 --> 00:08:59,710
I believe in you.

109
00:09:00,669 --> 00:09:03,505
What if I get up there, and there's nothing?

110
00:09:03,589 --> 00:09:06,967
Well, that's a risk you'll have to take.

111
00:09:07,051 --> 00:09:08,469
Hey, you're lucky.

112
00:09:08,552 --> 00:09:12,056
I haven't even seen
anything resembling my crystal yet.

113
00:09:12,139 --> 00:09:13,432
Good luck.

114
00:09:22,232 --> 00:09:25,360
A whistling? I can't hear anything.

115
00:09:36,538 --> 00:09:38,582
You think it's your crystal?

116
00:09:44,046 --> 00:09:46,757
Gungi, no. You'll never make it.

117
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:49,259
You'll freeze to death if you fall in.

118
00:09:49,343 --> 00:09:51,345
You need to be patient.

119
00:09:51,428 --> 00:09:54,640
See how the sun is setting
and moving away from the lake?

120
00:09:54,723 --> 00:09:58,018
Just like the door we came through,
it's freezing over again.

121
00:09:58,102 --> 00:09:59,770
Once the water freezes over,

122
00:09:59,853 --> 00:10:01,313
you will have very little time

123
00:10:01,396 --> 00:10:03,941
to get your crystal and get out.

124
00:10:05,609 --> 00:10:10,197
Now, excuse me. I have a crystal to find,
and I'm running out of time.

125
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,949
Good luck, Gungi.

126
00:10:51,572 --> 00:10:55,492
This whole thing is ridiculous.
I don't even think there are any crystals.

127
00:10:55,868 --> 00:10:56,952
You hear me?

128
00:10:57,035 --> 00:11:00,664
You just have us walking in circles
until we freeze to death.

129
00:11:00,747 --> 00:11:03,333
I'm never going to find a crystal. Never!

130
00:11:06,545 --> 00:11:07,880
Ah!

131
00:11:15,846 --> 00:11:17,639
Now what?

132
00:11:21,894 --> 00:11:24,897
Looks like I'm the first back
with my crystal. Hmm.

133
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:26,106
That wasn't so hard.

134
00:11:26,565 --> 00:11:27,816
And the others?

135
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:31,945
Who knows? I didn't want to gloat
since I found mine so quickly.

136
00:11:34,823 --> 00:11:36,408
Show us.

137
00:11:44,249 --> 00:11:46,418
A crystal, you have found.

138
00:11:46,501 --> 00:11:48,170
Water, you have brought.

139
00:11:48,253 --> 00:11:52,549
But that's impossible.
It was my crystal, I was sure of it.

140
00:11:52,925 --> 00:11:54,009
Hmm.

141
00:11:54,092 --> 00:11:58,180
So certain, were you.
Go back, and closer you must look.

142
00:11:59,306 --> 00:12:01,975
But the door is already half-closed.

143
00:12:02,434 --> 00:12:04,311
Then you better hurry.

144
00:12:24,414 --> 00:12:25,499
Oh!

145
00:12:29,503 --> 00:12:32,631
You can do this, Katooni. You can do it.

146
00:12:36,301 --> 00:12:37,678
That's impossible.

147
00:12:37,803 --> 00:12:42,015
It's saying there's crystals everywhere,
but I can't see anything!

148
00:12:42,099 --> 00:12:44,142
Where? Which way?

149
00:12:44,518 --> 00:12:45,644
Ugh!

150
00:12:45,686 --> 00:12:47,354
You're useless.

151
00:12:47,479 --> 00:12:49,648
Stupid, useless, dumb thing,

152
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:51,817
can't even find a simple small crystal !

153
00:12:51,942 --> 00:12:53,318
Ugh!

154
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:23,849
There's so many.

155
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:26,852
How am I supposed to know
which one is mine?

156
00:13:27,769 --> 00:13:29,354
It's hopeless.

157
00:13:30,188 --> 00:13:31,690
Hopeless.

158
00:14:20,238 --> 00:14:23,116
Well, that's going to take too long.

159
00:15:05,158 --> 00:15:06,868
I'm not afraid.

160
00:15:06,993 --> 00:15:09,037
I can do this.

161
00:15:09,162 --> 00:15:11,164
I'm a Jedi.

162
00:15:11,248 --> 00:15:15,043
I'm one with the Force,
and the Force will guide me.

163
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:43,530
I'm running out of time. Where is it?

164
00:15:46,950 --> 00:15:48,702
Come on, Zatt.

165
00:15:48,785 --> 00:15:53,498
You're going to have to trust yourself
instead of relying on technology.

166
00:15:53,582 --> 00:15:55,208
You can do it.

167
00:16:01,298 --> 00:16:02,591
I can feel it.

168
00:16:02,674 --> 00:16:04,426
It's close.

169
00:16:04,509 --> 00:16:06,303
I can sense it.

170
00:16:06,386 --> 00:16:08,013
I can sense it.

171
00:16:13,518 --> 00:16:15,353
That must be it.

172
00:17:51,491 --> 00:17:52,993
Oh, great!

173
00:17:53,076 --> 00:17:54,244
Ah!

174
00:18:06,006 --> 00:18:08,508
Oh, no. It's a dead end.

175
00:18:10,844 --> 00:18:12,512
Is anyone there?

176
00:18:12,596 --> 00:18:13,763
Can you hear me?

177
00:18:14,264 --> 00:18:18,435
Great! I have my crystal,
but I'll never get out of this place!

178
00:18:25,191 --> 00:18:28,570
Well done, Gungi, but two still remain.

179
00:18:37,037 --> 00:18:39,789
I'm running in circles!

180
00:18:39,873 --> 00:18:42,542
Petro! Petro!

181
00:18:44,711 --> 00:18:47,589
-Katooni?
-Petro, I'm trapped.

182
00:18:47,714 --> 00:18:49,215
Can you help me get out?

183
00:18:49,299 --> 00:18:50,383
I...

184
00:18:50,425 --> 00:18:53,720
I can't. I still haven't found my crystal.

185
00:18:53,762 --> 00:18:55,889
Petro, you can't leave me!

186
00:18:57,474 --> 00:18:59,768
-I have to go.
-Petro, no!

187
00:19:01,728 --> 00:19:04,397
Petro! Petro!

188
00:19:08,068 --> 00:19:12,072
-Will they make it, Master?
-We should help them.

189
00:19:12,155 --> 00:19:16,409
Left the cave, you have.
Help them, you will not.

190
00:19:19,788 --> 00:19:21,331
Come on !

191
00:19:40,141 --> 00:19:43,061
-Katooni. Katooni !
-Petro?

192
00:19:43,103 --> 00:19:45,230
-Petro!
-There's no time.

193
00:19:45,271 --> 00:19:48,108
Put your hand on the ice.
Together, we can break it.

194
00:20:04,999 --> 00:20:08,920
I knew you'd come back.
Come on. The doors are closing.

195
00:20:09,963 --> 00:20:11,464
Petro?

196
00:20:11,506 --> 00:20:15,301
Go ahead. I think I see something.

197
00:20:15,427 --> 00:20:16,928
But it's too late.

198
00:20:16,970 --> 00:20:18,805
Trust me. Go!

199
00:20:37,323 --> 00:20:40,535
I have my crystal, but Petro is still inside.

200
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:42,996
Give up on your friend, do not.

201
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:59,846
Petro! You made it!

202
00:20:59,929 --> 00:21:01,681
How did he break the ice?

203
00:21:01,806 --> 00:21:04,350
Only water made solid was the door.

204
00:21:04,476 --> 00:21:07,520
Easy to break, if you have the will.

205
00:21:08,938 --> 00:21:11,357
You said we would be trapped.

206
00:21:11,441 --> 00:21:15,945
Not by the cave, you were,
but by your mind.

207
00:21:16,029 --> 00:21:17,322
Lessons you have learned.

208
00:21:17,947 --> 00:21:19,949
Find courage, you did.

209
00:21:21,201 --> 00:21:22,368
Hope,

210
00:21:23,620 --> 00:21:24,954
patience,

211
00:21:26,623 --> 00:21:28,458
Trust,

212
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:30,001
confidence,

213
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,797
and selflessness. Yes?

214
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:42,472
Take your crystals back to the Temple
and keep them safe, young Jedi.

215
00:21:44,474 --> 00:21:46,643
- So exciting !
- Yes!

216
00:21:46,726 --> 00:21:48,144
All right!

217
00:21:48,168 --> 00:21:53,168
http://hiqve.com/

